reviewText: Not worth your money.  Any movie that has Diora Baird in it I would have expected much better
DVD arrive in great condition n plays fine.

Dale  Coop (Aaron Nee) and Mad Dog (Shea Whigham) kidnap Lulu (Lena Gwendolyn Hill) for the big score. Meanwhile Dale's brother naive Roy (Adam Nee) comes home to Dale's apartment where he gets beat up because he is mistaken for his brother,

The plot takes a number of twists and winds up in South of Heaven Texas.

This is a quirky film that takes place in the 1950's or so. The scenes are fake looking painted stage sets. At times the film takes on a cartoon atmosphere, other times it is noir. It is a black comedy that fans of ??? I am not sure what...would appreciate this film.

Guide: F-word, brief sex, brief rape, brief nudity.
This was a great little movie! Very likable, interesting, weird characters. Great story. Shea Whigham was amazing! Lots of great lines in this one!
